CNCP v1 24102
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9647: `defineComponent` prop types are broken in \"Functional Signature\" mode",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:26.948133+00:00",
  "text": "`defineComponent` prop types are broken in \"Functional Signature\" mode\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.8\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI have basically taken an example from the [docs](https://vuejs.org/api/general.html#function-signature) and simplified it a bit:\r\n```vue\r\n<script lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport { defineComponent } from 'vue';\r\n\r\nexport default defineComponent(\r\n  <T>(_: { msg: T; list: T[] }) => () => null,\r\n  { props: [\"msg\", \"list\"] },\r\n)\r\n</script>\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nI expected the type of this component after import to be the following:\r\n```typescript\r\nimport Comp from \"./Comp.vue\";\r\ntype Temp = typeof Comp;\r\n//   ^? type Temp = <T>(props: { msg: T; list: [T] } & {}) => any\r\n```\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`any` is replacing the `T` parameters:\r\n```typescript\r\nimport Comp from \"./Comp.vue\";\r\ntype Temp = typeof Comp;\r\n//   ^? type Temp = (props: { msg: any; list: any } & {}) => any\r\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nA workaround is casting `props` to `never[]`:\r\n```vue\r\n<script lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport { defineComponent } from 'vue';\r\n\r\nexport default defineComponent(\r\n  <T>(_: { msg: T; list: T[] }) => () => null,\r\n  { props: [\"msg\", \"list\"] as never[] },\r\n)\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen `typeOf Comp` returns expected type.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: types",
    "has workaround"
  ],
